WEBVTT

00:10.184 --> 00:11.185
BONHAM:Whoa.

00:11.228 --> 00:12.621
What's going? What is this?

00:12.664 --> 00:14.275
40 years.
We're celebrating.

00:14.318 --> 00:16.625
Is that scarlet sage?

00:16.668 --> 00:17.626
Sure is.

00:17.669 --> 00:18.757
I loved how it grew wild

00:18.801 --> 00:20.020
near the porch at home.

00:20.063 --> 00:21.891
AUGUST:
Where do you think we got it?

00:21.934 --> 00:23.719
Little anniversary trespassing.

00:23.762 --> 00:26.417
He's kidding.
You are, right?

00:26.461 --> 00:29.072
Okay, scooch. I mean,
this all looks beautiful,

00:29.116 --> 00:31.118
but, uh, we're a little
particular about our bacon.

00:31.161 --> 00:34.034
No, Mama, please,
go and relax outside.

00:34.077 --> 00:36.471
We know how Dad
likes bacon.

00:36.514 --> 00:39.039
Why don't we get you
situated outside?

00:39.082 --> 00:40.953
Outside.[overlapping chatter]

00:40.997 --> 00:42.607
BONHAM: Make 'em happy.
Go outside. Come on.Go, the two of you.

00:42.651 --> 00:43.826
Happy anniversary.

00:43.869 --> 00:45.262
Thank you very much.Thanks.

00:45.306 --> 00:47.090
BONHAM: Y'all are the best.ABELINE: It's very sweet.

00:47.134 --> 00:48.439
BONHAM
I guess.

00:48.483 --> 00:50.485
Let's go.
Thank you, Augie.
Thanks.

00:50.528 --> 00:53.314
Is anyone else
getting cold feet?

00:53.357 --> 00:55.185
Mawline seemed a little bit...

00:55.229 --> 00:57.187
Trust me, after all
they've gone through lately...All right. Enjoy.

00:57.231 --> 01:00.016
...getting showered
with love

01:00.060 --> 01:02.366
is exactly what Mama
needs right now.

01:02.410 --> 01:04.281
Uh, let's just go over
the plan again.

01:04.325 --> 01:05.848
Yeah, yeah. I'm-I'm gonna
get the bubbly.[cell phone chimes]

01:05.891 --> 01:07.632
Trey actually told me
about a place here in town

01:07.676 --> 01:09.982
that deals rare wines, so...
He's in Vegas

01:10.026 --> 01:12.550
with his mom, but...

01:12.594 --> 01:13.899
Bubbles?Yes.

01:13.943 --> 01:15.684
Good. Great. Check.
Uh, kids?

01:15.727 --> 01:17.599
Don't ruin the surprise.
Uh, be on time.Mm-hmm.

01:17.642 --> 01:20.036
Mm-hmm.
And, uh, yeah, I think

01:20.080 --> 01:22.038
we got it.And we may have a little

01:22.082 --> 01:23.692
something else planned
for them as well.

01:23.735 --> 01:24.997
Yeah? Awesome.
STELLA: Mm-hmm.

01:25.041 --> 01:26.347
Oh, one more thing, uh,

01:26.390 --> 01:28.000
Cassie wants to tag along today,

01:28.044 --> 01:30.177
so we'll have all hands on deck,
plus one.

01:30.220 --> 01:31.569
Well, she can ride with me.

01:31.613 --> 01:33.789
Love to get a chance to meet
your newest victim.

01:33.832 --> 01:34.703
WALKER:
Great. Let's do it.

01:34.746 --> 01:36.052
Divide and conquer.

01:36.096 --> 01:38.315
Divide and conquer.Divide and conquer.

01:38.359 --> 01:40.796
Yeah.

01:40.839 --> 01:42.972
Hey, Pops. I'm just, uh...

01:43.015 --> 01:45.540
Listen, uh, these windows
aren't double-paned,

01:45.583 --> 01:47.716
and you already can't whisper
worth a damn, son.

01:47.759 --> 01:49.544
Yeah, that-that's...
that's nothing.

01:49.587 --> 01:50.849
Okay, listen,

01:50.893 --> 01:52.590
if you're really
looking for something

01:52.634 --> 01:55.854
to get your mother, there is
one thing that you can do.

01:55.898 --> 01:57.160
Great, sure, anything.

01:57.204 --> 01:58.553
Well...

01:58.596 --> 02:00.729
Abby hasn't been the same
since everything

02:00.772 --> 02:02.252
with Geraldine went down.

02:02.296 --> 02:05.037
You know, we all...

02:05.081 --> 02:06.430
feel the way we
feel about that,

02:06.474 --> 02:10.217
but your mother... [sighs]

02:10.260 --> 02:12.175
Well, hell, the one thing
that'll make this day

02:12.219 --> 02:14.525
really special...

02:14.569 --> 02:16.353
is Geraldine
giving her a chance.

02:17.876 --> 02:19.530
Yes, sir.So, you're working on that?

02:19.574 --> 02:20.662
I will do.
All right.

02:25.188 --> 02:26.407
[door opens]

02:26.450 --> 02:27.712
[Gale sighs]

02:30.280 --> 02:32.630
That was so nice, huh?
Just three of us

02:32.674 --> 02:34.328
getting out of town
for a couple days.

02:34.371 --> 02:35.894
Yeah. Yeah.

02:35.938 --> 02:37.896
I know it was a little tense
with Denise.

02:37.940 --> 02:41.509
I get it. It's-it's a lot
to process.Yeah.

02:41.552 --> 02:43.337
You know, waking up
in your 30s,

02:43.380 --> 02:47.123
learning that you have
a sister and that...

02:47.167 --> 02:48.907
Well, you know.

02:48.951 --> 02:50.779
Yeah. She'll come around.It's... Yeah.

02:50.822 --> 02:52.346
I know that.
Yeah.

02:52.389 --> 02:53.912
I mean, Lord knows I'm

02:53.956 --> 02:57.046
still wrapping my head
around it, but

02:57.089 --> 02:59.440
I am glad that
we're trying.
[sighs]

02:59.483 --> 03:00.789
Me, too.

03:00.832 --> 03:03.357
Well, thank you...
Aw.

03:03.400 --> 03:04.445
...for everything.Of course, of course.

03:04.488 --> 03:06.751
Ah.

03:06.795 --> 03:08.362
Um, hey, you know what, though?

03:08.405 --> 03:09.928
You and I haven't
really had any

03:09.972 --> 03:13.062
mother-daughter time,
just, you know, just one-on-one.

03:13.105 --> 03:16.718
Mother-daughter.
Wow, that's... still so...

03:16.761 --> 03:18.459
[laughs]...so crazy. Um,

03:18.502 --> 03:20.243
Yeah, no, I guess you're right.

03:20.287 --> 03:21.679
Why don't you
come on by tonight?

03:21.723 --> 03:23.812
I'll pull out
some family recipes

03:23.855 --> 03:25.683
and, you know, read you in on
some secrets.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.427
Yeah. I think I'd like that.

03:30.471 --> 03:32.473
All right.

03:32.516 --> 03:33.822
All right. Bye, honey.

03:33.865 --> 03:36.172
Bye.

03:36.216 --> 03:38.827
You really know
your Syrahs.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.352
[sighs] I guess I

03:42.396 --> 03:45.137
just like to think about
the life of wine,

03:45.181 --> 03:46.748
how it's a living thing.

03:46.791 --> 03:49.098
I like
to think about

03:49.141 --> 03:51.535
what was going on

03:51.579 --> 03:54.016
the year the grapes
were growing, and...

03:55.626 --> 03:57.019
Are you really buying this?

03:57.062 --> 03:58.629
Seriously?

03:58.673 --> 04:00.283
There's, like,
one movie about wine,

04:00.327 --> 04:03.243
and you, a wine person,
haven't seen it?

04:03.286 --> 04:05.201
Uh...Oh, come on,
it's Paul Giamatti.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.072
It's a great film.
It's Sideways.

04:07.116 --> 04:09.814
My dad's a real bourbon guy,
so the fact he brings up

04:09.858 --> 04:11.468
this wine that they toasted

04:11.512 --> 04:14.079
every time that he talks
about their wedding...

04:14.123 --> 04:15.429
I mean, it must be special.

04:15.472 --> 04:16.865
That or

04:16.908 --> 04:18.867
just because it gives my mom
the giggles.

04:18.910 --> 04:20.912
[laughs]
I...

04:20.956 --> 04:23.741
Oh, the Chalamet Esprit Brut
Vintage '82.

04:23.785 --> 04:26.962
Bottle that nice would give
anybody the giggles.

04:27.005 --> 04:29.094
It's a wonderful gift,
if you can find it.

04:29.138 --> 04:31.880
[chuckles] So... can you get it?

04:31.923 --> 04:34.056
For you, I'll see what I can do.

04:34.099 --> 04:36.014
I'll say this,

04:36.058 --> 04:37.625
they're lucky to have
a son like you.

04:37.668 --> 04:39.279
Well...

04:39.322 --> 04:42.543
I'll place some calls
with local collectors.

04:43.935 --> 04:45.633
If you'll leave me
your info...
Yeah.

04:45.676 --> 04:46.938
Uh, William.

04:46.982 --> 04:49.245
Well, Liam.
Everybody calls me Liam.

04:49.289 --> 04:51.247
Um, but, I'm sorry,
I didn't get your name.

04:51.291 --> 04:52.466
[chuckles] Yeah.

04:52.509 --> 04:54.250
Ben.

04:54.294 --> 04:55.730
Cass.

04:55.773 --> 04:57.514
You two know each other.

04:57.558 --> 05:00.169
I-I didn't realize
you worked here.

05:00.212 --> 05:03.172
Clearly, given that you're here.

05:03.215 --> 05:05.305
LIAM: Oh.
You two know each other

05:05.348 --> 05:07.307
in-in a not great way.

05:07.350 --> 05:09.047
I just wasn't sure where you...

05:09.091 --> 05:11.485
No, of course.
The city's chock-full

05:11.528 --> 05:13.095
of specialty
wine and spirit shops.

05:13.138 --> 05:14.836
[chuckles]
I mean, it kind of is.

05:14.879 --> 05:16.272
BEN:
I'm sorry.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.100
I'm late for my
lunch break. Um...

05:18.143 --> 05:19.710
My colleague
will help you.

05:19.754 --> 05:21.277
LIAM:
Yeah, I...

05:21.321 --> 05:22.626
[sighs]

05:22.670 --> 05:24.193
Okay.

05:24.236 --> 05:26.978
What the hell
was that?

05:27.022 --> 05:30.504
That was everyone's
favorite Perez.

05:30.547 --> 05:32.070
My brother.

05:34.421 --> 05:36.423
♪

05:47.434 --> 05:48.391
[burps]

05:48.435 --> 05:50.088
Oh.

05:50.132 --> 05:51.133
You're gross.

05:51.176 --> 05:53.091
Speaking of gross.
How's the drama?

05:53.135 --> 05:54.658
I'm sorry, the what?

05:54.702 --> 05:56.704
Oh, you know, that little
love triangle you seem to find

05:56.747 --> 05:58.096
yourself in that,
you know, threatens

05:58.140 --> 05:59.707
to destroy not only my band,

05:59.750 --> 06:01.491
but, like, the only
real guy friends

06:01.535 --> 06:03.014
I've had in a while.

06:03.058 --> 06:04.407
Not to make it
about me or anything.

06:04.451 --> 06:06.453
Yeah, definitely
not making it about you.

06:07.845 --> 06:10.413
But I think I've had
a breakthrough,

06:10.457 --> 06:12.328
and not just about boys.

06:12.372 --> 06:15.331
I'm at a fork in the road
in a lot of ways.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.724
You'll get it
when you're a senior.

06:16.767 --> 06:18.290
Yeah?
Mm-hmm.

06:18.334 --> 06:19.335
All this stuff

06:19.379 --> 06:20.771
for Gramps and Mawline,

06:20.815 --> 06:22.599
everything that they've
been through.

06:22.643 --> 06:24.862
Yeah, horse races,
murder charges.

06:24.906 --> 06:26.690
We're here because
of a turning point.

06:26.734 --> 06:27.996
Think about it.

06:28.039 --> 06:29.606
On what was maybe

06:29.650 --> 06:32.043
one of the most interesting
nights of Mawline's life,

06:32.087 --> 06:35.133
just as she was celebrating
her engagement to Marv,

06:35.177 --> 06:37.658
she met Gramps,
and everything changed.

06:37.701 --> 06:39.224
Okay?

06:39.268 --> 06:41.270
Okay, so...

06:41.313 --> 06:43.968
Todd or Colton
or "choosing myself."

06:44.012 --> 06:46.536
Am I staying here or going
to freaking Oregon for college?

06:46.580 --> 06:47.711
All I'm saying

06:47.755 --> 06:49.931
is fate, like, butted in

06:49.974 --> 06:52.194
and basically pointed the way
for Mawline,

06:52.237 --> 06:54.022
and 40 years later,

06:54.065 --> 06:55.284
here we are.

06:55.327 --> 06:56.590
Something happened that night,

06:56.633 --> 06:58.505
and Mawline listened.

06:58.548 --> 07:01.595
So, I'm just gonna wait
for a sign to guide me.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.773
What?

07:05.816 --> 07:07.601
Oh, nothing. I was gonna burp,

07:07.644 --> 07:09.167
but it feels like you were
saying something important,

07:09.211 --> 07:10.255
so I refrained.

07:10.299 --> 07:12.823
[chuckles]

07:12.867 --> 07:14.912
[hammering]

07:16.740 --> 07:18.742
[chuckles] Hey!

07:18.786 --> 07:20.091
Check it out.

07:20.135 --> 07:21.702
What do you think?CASSIE: Wow.

07:21.745 --> 07:24.008
It's, uh, subtle,
understated.

07:24.052 --> 07:25.227
I love it.
Yeah.

07:25.270 --> 07:27.534
I'm glad that someone's
making progress.

07:27.577 --> 07:29.492
Hey, uh, you get
that champagne?

07:29.536 --> 07:31.929
Uh, we ran into a little issue.

07:31.973 --> 07:35.063
[chuckles] He's being nice.
We didn't get it.

07:35.106 --> 07:37.065
We had a...
Okay.

07:37.108 --> 07:38.980
...little run-in
with my big brother

07:39.023 --> 07:41.373
which sent the
whole thing, well,

07:41.417 --> 07:42.549
sideways,

07:42.592 --> 07:43.811
which is a movie

07:43.854 --> 07:45.943
any so-called wine person
should've seen.

07:45.987 --> 07:47.858
Uh, hold on a second.
Let's back it up.

07:47.902 --> 07:50.774
You have a brother?
And he lives in Austin?

07:50.818 --> 07:53.516
Uh, how am I just
finding this out?

07:53.560 --> 07:55.431
Well, you know what,
didn't really come up

07:55.475 --> 07:56.867
between the, "Hey, get in
the trunk,"

07:56.911 --> 07:58.565
and the, "Oh, no, I've made
a traumatic discovery

07:58.608 --> 08:00.523
about my partner," so...

08:00.567 --> 08:02.482
But, yes, I do.

08:02.525 --> 08:04.875
I'm gathering that you two
aren't really close?

08:04.919 --> 08:06.921
LIAM: Cordi, can I actually
pick your brain

08:06.964 --> 08:08.575
just for a second?Yeah.

08:08.618 --> 08:10.925
Alone. Uh...
about the banner.

08:10.968 --> 08:12.404
About the...Um...

08:12.448 --> 08:13.493
What's wrong
with the banner?

08:13.536 --> 08:15.233
I-I saw
what went down

08:15.277 --> 08:17.801
between her
and her brother

08:17.845 --> 08:18.976
today, and
I think what

08:19.020 --> 08:20.151
she may need
is a little less

08:20.195 --> 08:22.937
boom, smash, overshare,

08:22.980 --> 08:24.242
and a little more gentle.

08:24.286 --> 08:26.549
[laughs] Thanks, Liam,
'cause, mm,

08:26.593 --> 08:27.855
that sounded
a little bit like a jab.

08:27.898 --> 08:28.986
It's not a...
[clears throat]

08:29.030 --> 08:30.684
Divide and conquer,

08:30.727 --> 08:32.207
remember?

08:32.250 --> 08:33.948
How are things going
with the whole

08:33.991 --> 08:35.515
reuniting of Mom and Geri?

08:35.558 --> 08:36.951
It's delicate
right now, you know.

08:36.994 --> 08:39.431
I called her earlier.
Haven't heard back,

08:39.475 --> 08:41.303
but, uh...

08:41.346 --> 08:43.740
Yeah. You know what, why don't,
why don't you let me take over

08:43.784 --> 08:46.874
